This paper discusses the analysis of network delay and Age of Information (AoI) in a multi-hop satellite network, which involves the transmission of data from one satellite to another. This topic is closely related to the field of computer networks (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also models the satellite network as a queue network of M/M/1 systems, which is a common approach in the field of control systems (cs.SY) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the design of multi-hop satellite networks for latency-sensitive applications, which is relevant to the field of computer architecture (cs.AR).
